@startuml SD05_Vote
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
title SD-05: Upvote/Downvote (Redis + Kafka Fan-Out)

actor "User" as U
participant "Astro\nFrontend" as FE
participant "Envoy\nGateway" as GW
participant "Vote\nService" as VOTE
database "Redis\n(db0)" as REDIS
queue "Kafka" as KAFKA
database "pg-platform" as DB
participant "Post\nService" as POST
participant "User\nService" as USER
participant "Spam\nDetection" as SPAM

U -> FE : Click upvote on post
FE -> GW : POST /api/votes\n{target_id, target_type: "post",\ndirection: "up"} + JWT
GW -> GW : Validate JWT + rate limit

GW -> VOTE : gRPC CastVote()
VOTE -> REDIS : GET vote:user123:post456
alt Already voted same direction
    VOTE --> GW : 200 OK (no-op, idempotent)
    GW --> FE : JSON {score: unchanged}
    FE --> U : No visual change
else New vote or direction change
    VOTE -> REDIS : SET vote:user123:post456 = "up"
    VOTE -> REDIS : INCR post:456:score
    VOTE --> GW : 200 OK {new_score}
    GW --> FE : JSON {score: 43}
    FE --> U : Update vote arrow + score

    == Async Persistence + Fan-Out ==
    VOTE ->> KAFKA : Publish "VoteCreated"\n{user, target, direction, author_id}
    VOTE ->> DB : Persist vote record (async)

    KAFKA ->> POST : Consume event
    POST -> POST : Update post score in pg-post

    KAFKA ->> USER : Consume event
    USER -> USER : Recalculate author karma

    KAFKA ->> SPAM : Consume event
    SPAM -> SPAM : Check for vote\nmanipulation patterns
end
@enduml
